# Kingdom 1516 frontend — environment template (Story 3.2).
#
# Copy to site/.env locally and set the real value; site/.env is git-ignored and
# must never be committed. This default is deliberately fake so it fails loudly if
# it ever reaches a live build.
#
# PUBLIC_DIRECTUS_URL is the leader-auth API base (the Caddy admin subdomain, https).
# It is PUBLIC (baked into client JS, not a secret). Astro exposes PUBLIC_* vars to
# the browser via import.meta.env — see src/lib/directus.ts. `npm run build` is green
# with this placeholder; the real value is a LAUNCH blocker (Open Q1 domain), not a
# build blocker, and must equal the live DIRECTUS_DOMAIN or CORS/login breaks.
PUBLIC_DIRECTUS_URL=https://admin.kingdom1516.example
